
// The code uses the [sockets.signal] slot to send a signal to a session, transforming the specified children [args] nodes into JSON. It includes three arguments: [function_result], [invocation], and [file], which are dynamically retrieved from other nodes using expressions. This allows for real-time communication, where the specified session receives the JSON-encoded data.
sockets.signal:x:@.session
   args
      function_result:x:@config.get
      invocation:x:@execute/*/json
      file:x:@execute/*/workflow
